    "severity": "critical",
    "description": "The containsPosition() method uses '>=' instead of '>' when checking if a position is at the end edge of a range. The docstring explicitly states 'If the position is at the edges, will return true', but the current check excludes positions at the end column. This breaks containment semantics for decorations, find-and-replace highlighting, and bracket matching that rely on inclusive edge behavior.",
    "fix_patch": "--- a/src/vs/editor/common/core/range.ts
