    "file": "src/vs/base/common/strings.ts",
    "line": 226,
    "severity": "critical",
    "description": "The matchCase flag logic is inverted. The 'i' RegExp flag means case-INsensitive matching. When options.matchCase is true, we need case-SENSITIVE matching (no 'i' flag). When false, we need case-INSENSITIVE matching ('i' flag). The current code adds 'i' when matchCase is true, which is backwards. This breaks all case-sensitive/insensitive find operations, affecting textModelSearch.ts which calls createRegExp().",
    "fix_patch": "--- a/src/vs/base/common/strings.ts
+++ b/src/vs/base/common/strings.ts
@@ -223,7 +223,7 @@
 	if (options.global) {
 		modifiers += 'g';
 	}
-	if (options.matchCase) {
+	if (!options.matchCase) {
 		modifiers += 'i';
 	}
 	if (options.multiline) {
"
